START

a method that takes an array of integers, and returns a new array with every other element

SET iterator = 1
SET original_array = array of integers
SET new_array to an empty array

WHILE iterator < length of original_array
  IF iterator is even
    add the integer within original_array at position of iterator to new_array
  ELSE go the the next iteration

  iterator = iterator + 1

PRINT new_array

END
